Rating: 4
This is one of the best hot fudge sauce recipes I've even made. Years ago, I worked at Inverness Country Club and they were reknown for their signature dessert, The Hot Fudge Nut Ball. (French vanilla ice cream rolled in toasted pecans, place in a champagne glass and drenched in hot fudge........ a dessert to die for. This hot fudge recipe is the closest I've found to being there. Enjoy!!!!

Rating: 3
This is an excellent hot fudge sauce and very simple to make. I makes a wonderful sundae. Stores in the refrigerator well and reheats well in the microwave (30 seconds on high). A definite hit for a chocolate lovers.